Config - heartbeat address
item.description: IP address the node should listen for heartbeats

item.name: Config - heartbeat interval
item.description: Interval in milliseconds in which heartbeats are sent

item.name: Config - heartbeat mode
item.description: May be either multicast or mesh. In case of multicast, all cluster nodes must be in the same subnet

item.name: Config - heartbeat port
item.description: Multicast Port for cluster-state communication. Applies only when mode is multicast

item.name: Config - heartbeat protocol
item.description:
Hearbeat protocol version to be used by cluster. Should be one of v1, v2 or none.
v1 = Original protocol version v2 = Expandable cluster size protocol version (depends on paxos-max-cluster-size) none = Used only for dynamically changing protocol

item.name: Config - heartbeat timeout
item.description: Number of missing heartbeats after which the remote node will be declared dead

item.name: Config - info threads
item.description: Number of threads to create to process info requests

item.name: Config - mesh seed address port
item.description: Mesh address and port info for seed server(s). These are other addresses from the cluster that Aerospike will bootstrap from. A new line is required for each additional boot strap. Applies only when mode is mesh

item.name: Config - microbenchmarks
item.description: Enable microbenchmark for additional logging, in order to investigate complex issues/slow transactions

item.name: Config - migrate max num incoming
item.description: Maximum number of partitions a node can receiving records from at any given time

item.name: Config - migrate read sleep
item.description: Time to sleep, in milliseconds, when migrate-xmit-priority is reached. Will not sleep if migrate-xmit-priority is set to 0

item.name: Config - migrate threads
item.description: Number of threads per server allocated for data migration

item.name: Config - migrate xmit hwm
item.description: Used to throttle network i/o during migrations by limiting the number of 'in-flight' records

item.name: Config - migrate xmit lwn
item.description: Resumes migrations when the number of 'in-flight' records fall bellow this configuration's value

item.name: Config - migrate xmit priority
item.description: Number of records to ship before sleeping for 'migrate-xmit-sleep' milliseconds

item.name: Config - migrate xmit sleep
item.description: Time to sleep, in milliseconds, when migrate-xmit-priority is reached. Will not sleep if migrate-xmit-priority is set to 0

item.name: Config - nsup period
item.description: The interval (secs) at which expiration/eviction thread (namespace supervisor) wakes up

item.name: Config - nsup startup evict
item.description: Do evictions (not expiration) at boot time also in case the memory limits are breached

item.name: Config - paxos max cluster size
item.description: Maximum number of nodes allowed in cluster

item.name: Config - paxos protocol
item.description:
Paxos protocol version to be used in cluster. Should be one of v1, v2, v3, v4 or none.
v1 = Original protocol version v2 = Expandable cluster size protocol version v3 = SIndex query node protocol version v4 = Rack Aware protocol version none = Used only for dynamically changing protocol

item.name: Config - paxos retransmit period
item.description: Tuning parameter for how often to run retransmit checks for paxos

item.name: Config - paxos single replica limit
item.description: If the cluster size is less than or equal to this value, only one copy of the data (no replicas) will be kept in the cluster

item.name: Config - pidfile
item.description: File to store the PID of the daemon

item.name: Config - prole extra ttl
item.description: Seconds beyond expiry time after which we garbage collect. To be used when investigating if there are orphan replicas

item.name: Config - proto fd idle ms
item.description: Time in milliseconds to wait before reaping connections

item.description: Maximum number of open file descriptors opened on behalf of client connections
